It's time to tear down our bedroom. The last room in the house where, apart from a bit of decorating, nothing has been done yet.
The disgusting electric fireplace and fireplace floor must go. We need to enclose the fireplace, replace the flaking plaster, and smooth it out. Then build a custom closet.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch...
The dirty part of the job is done.
In the back of the chimney, we found a few dead birds, very dry :(
Everything ready for the plasterer next week
The small side niche turned out well
Here comes a new wardrobe (but we haven't even started with the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heating!
And we even thought of installing this nice little exhaust flap, so the chimney doesn't get damp
The chimney sweep has installed the covering and hood. Now it should be a bit safer for the crows who like to nest up there 🪺
The plasterer is finished. Tomorrow the floor will be laid!
The underlayment is in place, I have cobbled together a cork-extractor made of sawdust and toilet paper rolls for the vacuum cleaner 😂
The floor sections are finished and can be laid. We're taking a tea break right now
Oh no. Today everything is going slowly because of super complicated cuts around the doorposts, so that we have a smooth transition to the corridor (where the floor will also be newly laid). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me
Done, but at the end! The crowning achievement was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
Still missing the floor in the hallway and all the baseboards. The decorator is coming in a month, so we have temporary rough-sawn look right now
A bit more DIY work in the evening to saw or chisel the lower sections around the doorposts where the floor will then fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlayment is now also in the hallway.
Yesterday, we finished the floor in the hallway! Then out at 5 am to pick up Item 1 at Heathrow, then a nap and a final push in the hallway, the baseboards are in place. The joints will be filled when the adhesive is dry
